title: ‘This is Donald Trump we haven’t seen before’: US President supports Iranian protesters
description: The Australian’s Foreign Editor Greg Sheridan says it is “fascinating” United States President Donald Trump is getting involved in Iran and the demonstrators.  “This is Donald Trump we haven’t seen before, it is very welcome that he is supporting the demonstrators,” Mr Sheridan said.  “I salute their magnificent courage.”

title: ‘Breathtaking’: Victoria has no ‘effective opposition' against Jacinta Allan
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes says there is no effective opposition in Victoria to push back against the Labor Party amid recent bushfires and public denouncement of the state’s Premier Jacinta Allan.

title: Expert analyses ‘key elements of repression’ of the Iranian Revolutionary Guard Corps
description: Strategic analysis Australia Director Peter Jennings details the key elements of repression used by the Iranian Revolutionary Guard.   “People have been talking about Israel very much now, they will have the right targets set to be able to know how to go after the key elements of repression of the Iranian Revolutionary Guard,” Mr Jennings told Sky News host Steve Price.  “I would love to know just what’s happening behind the scenes in terms of Israel talking to the United States.”

title: Iranians continue to protest in attempt to topple ‘despotic regime’
description: Sky News host Steve Price details how thousands of Iranians are taking to the streets to protest against the “despotic regime” of Iran.  “I want to turn to the unfolding story that is Iran now,” Mr Price said.  “Thousands and thousands of Iranians are taking to the streets daily in protest against the despotic regime that has ruled that country since 1979.”

title: Power cuts, lack of food supply and access to fuel key drivers of Iranian protests
description: Strategic analysis Australia Director Peter Jennings says cuts to power, food supply and fuel have led to the protests in Iran.  “Power cuts, food and fuel shortages, the regime has run its course,” Mr Jennings told Sky News host Steve Price.  “You can only get by with repression for so long.”

title: The meaning behind six-seven
description: Wordsmith and broadcaster Kel Richards analyses the top 10 banished words for 2026 and gets to the bottom behind the phrase “six seven”.

title: Donald Trump cancels ‘negotiations’ in the works with Iran amid killed protesters
description: Sky News Senior Reporter Caroline Marcus analyses United States President Donald Trump cancelling negotiations with Iran.  “He says he has cancelled negotiations,” Ms Marcus said.  “If he doesn’t do something at this stage, I think he would look a bit foolish after all the tough talk.”

title: National Party and One Nation wonder if tougher gun laws are ‘needed’ for Australia
description: Sky News host Steve Price says the National Party and One Nation are wondering whether tougher gun laws are “needed” for Australia.

title: Albanese govt wants law abiding gun owners to ‘pay’ for the actions of Bondi massacre
description: Former speaker of the house Bronwyn Bishop says the Albanese government wants law-abiding gun owners to “pay for the guilty actions” of the Bondi massacre shooters.

title: Donald Trump has talked about doing ‘anything’ to get ahold of Greenland
description: Wordsmith and Broadcaster Kel Richards says US President Donald Trump has talked about doing “anything” to get ahold of Greenland.

title: ‘Trump be trolling’: White House plays with the idea of securing Greenland
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says “Trump be trolling” with a recent post from the White House social media.  The post shows Donald Trump looking out a window at a map of Greenland.

title: Donald Trump’s political opponents continue to ‘fall’ for his trolling
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says Donald Trumps political opponents “fall” for his trolling.

title: Donald Trump has the ‘best social media game’ in the world
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says US President Donald Trump has the “best social media game” in the world.

title: Donald Trump drops a ‘huge distraction’ every time he wants to hide issues
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says US President Donald Trump drops a “huge distraction” every time he’s got an issue he wants to be hidden.

title: Freedom of speech is ‘inherent in a democracy’
description: Former speaker of the house Bronwyn Bishop says freedom of speech is something which is “inherent in a democracy”.
